<FIRST>r a AM-PartyBloodbath     08-29 0343</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Party Bloodbath,0354</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Say Spurned Husband Crashes Party and Opens Fire, Killing
Four</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man burst into a birthday party and opened
fire with a gun, killing his estranged wife and three other women
while seriously wounding two other people, authorities said Monday.
   Raymundo Navarro Jr. was arrested without resistance outside his
father's apartment, authorities and witnesses said. He was held
without bail for investigation of murder and of attempted murder.
   Maria Delia Navarro was celebrating her 27th birthday with about
20 family members and friends late Sunday when her estranged husband
burst in and began shooting a handgun, investigators said.
   Maria fell dead, as did Maria Garcia, 65, Leticia M. Dipp, 46,
and Francisca Arizpe, 62, said coroner's spokesman Bob Dambacher.
   ``I hid behind a cabinet when the man came in and started
shooting,'' said 12-year-old Francisco Amazcua. ``I saw people fall
to the floor. After he left, I ran into the bedroom and hid under
the bed with two other kids.''
   An unidentified woman was listed in critical condition at
County-USC Medical Center with gunshot wounds to the head, and a man
with a bullet wound in the abdomen was in serious condition, Los
Angeles County sheriff's investigators said.
   Partygoer Jesus Amezcua said someone telephoned Maria's apartment
about 11 p.m. Sunday to warn partygoers that Navarro, 26, was on his
way. Maria telephoned the 911 emergency line and said her husband
was coming to kill her, he said.
   The 911 operator told Maria to call back when Navarro arrived,
the partygoer said. Minutes later, Navarro invaded the party
carrying a gun, said Amezcua.
   The Sheriff's Department confirmed someone called the East Los
Angeles station prior to the shooting, but said it was unable to
give details about the conversation until the tape is located and
transcribed.
   ``He had a very bad temper. They used to fight a lot,'' said
Beatrice Palacios, 27, a longtime friend of the couple.
   The couple separated for about a year and Navarro has been
despondent about the breakup, friends said.
</TEXT>
