because of the scheduled extradition Wednesday of a Colombian drug
dealer.
   ``The Florida Department of Law Enforcement just feels a little
bit more comfortable, at least in these next few days, being a
little more cautious,'' the governor said.
   Brian Ballard, director of operations for Martinez, said the
governor's public schedule, which is normally published days in
advance for distribution to the press, will now be on a day-to-day
basis.
