<HEAD>Fort Worth School Teacher Fatally Stabbed Outside Classroom</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS grafs 2-3 to CORRECT spelling to `Glen' sted `Glenn' and
UPDATE with details.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A teacher was fatally stabbed Monday
outside her elementary school classroom on the city's southeast
side, police said.
   The 24-year-old teacher's name was being withheld pending
notification of her relatives, said Sgt. Billy Samuels. He said the
beginning teacher at Glen Park Elementary School had been stabbed
several times in the face and neck.
   ``It was pretty vicious,'' Samuels said.
   The woman apparently was attacked while moving school supplies to
her classroom, police said. Officers had no motive or suspect in the
killing. The woman's purse and car had not been taken and it did not
appear she had been sexually assaulted.
   Another teacher found the woman lying on steps outside her
classroom door about 12:40 p.m., Samuels said. No students were in
the school. The teachers had been preparing for fall classes to
start.
   The victim was pronounced dead about 2 p.m. at John Peter Smith
Hospital, Samuels said.
