<FIRST>r i PM-Thailand-USOperation     08-29 0202</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Thailand-US Operation,0207</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thai, U.S. Forces Storm Beach in War Games</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BAAN KHAO SAP, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American and Thai troops today
assaulted a beach along the Gulf of Thailand to climax six weeks of
war games codenamed ``Thalay Thai 89.''
   Several thousand local villagers watched as troops and tanks hit
the beach before sunrise from amphibious craft. Helicopters
clattered overhead, providing simulated support.
   A news release said 4,000 U.S. Marines and naval personnel from
both countries joined in the exercise, which also included maneuvers
on land after the landing.
   The Aug. 9 to Sept. 19 exercise is designed to strengthen combat
effectiveness and cooperation between the two countries, which have
close, longstanding ties.
   In the past, such joint war games, including the annual Cobra
Gold series, have drawn sharp criticism from neighboring communist
Indochina, which claims the United States is using such exercises to
reintroduce its military power into Southeast Asia.
   Thalay Thai 89 has included mine-laying and demolition
operations, navigation training, and anti-surface and anti-aircraft
warfare exercises.
   Taking part are 23 Thai and 26 U.S. naval vessels, including the
aircraft carrier USS Midway. American units include elements of the
Amphibious Ready Group ALFA and the 11th Marine Expeditionary Unit.
