<HEAD>Mother Gets Prison for Trading Daughter for Crack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman was sentenced to life in prison today for
giving her daughter to a rapist in exchange for drugs.
   Wayne County Circuit Court Judge James J. Rashid told Susan
Barbier, 29, that she had ``sunk to an intolerable level of
humanity'' in the May 1988 indident, for which she was convicted of
first-degree criminal sexual conduct.
   Rashid exceeded the sentencing guidelines, which called for 10 to
25 years in prison, saying Barbier has ``very little, if any at all,
potential for reformation.''
   Barbier gave her 13-year-old daughter over to Anthony Sawyer, who
raped the girl, then left the child alone while she went to get high
with Sawyer, police and court records showed.
   Sawyer, who had two previous rape convictions, was sentenced last
week to 40 to 60 years in prison for raping Barbier's daughter.
