<FILEID>AP-NR-08-29-89 1356EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>d w AM-VietnamRemains     08-29 0144</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Vietnam Remains,140</SECOND>
<HEAD>Remains of Vietnam Officer Identified</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The remains of an American serviceman returned
from Vietnam have been identified as an Air Force colonel from Iowa
who was reported missing in 1966, the Pentagon said Tuesday.
   The body of Merrill R. Lewis of Indianola, Iowa, was to be flown
home Wednesday after a military honors ceremony at Hickam Air Force
Base in Hawaii. The identity of a second serviceman was withheld at
the request of the family.
   Lewis was reported missing July 20, 1966, in North Vietnam.
   ``The remains of these men are the first two identified among 28
remains repatriated by Vietnam on June 21, 1989,'' a Pentagon
statement said. ``Other remains from that repatriation are still
undergoing analysis in an attempt to determine identification.''
   About 2,000 Americans are listed as missing in action from the
Vietnam War.

</TEXT>
