<SECOND>AM-Illinois Lotto,0218</SECOND>
<HEAD>Couple Claim $42 Million Illinois Lotto Prize</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto CX5</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A couple claimed Illinois' biggest single-winner
lottery jackpot _ $42 million _ and said Tuesday their priorities
are a quiet vacation and some investments.
   ``Like everyone else, we'd mapped out what we'd do if we won,''
said William Madigan. ``But today I can't remember a single thing we
talked about. My mind's a blank.''
   Madigan, 50, and his wife, Kathleen, 38, claimed the jackpot from
Saturday's Lotto drawing. They live in suburban Hometown with her
three children. The Madigans will receive 20 annual payments of $2.1
million.
   ``It's really very frightening, but at the same time it's a lot
of fun,'' Mrs. Madigan said. The couple said they hadn't given much
thought to spending the money beyond plans to buy a new car, remodel
their home and travel.
   Madigan, a supervisor for a security company, plans to keep his
job at least through the end of the year. Mrs. Madigan, a gift shop
clerk, said she will quit to spend more time with her children.
   The state's biggest jackpot is $69.9 million, awarded in an April
15 drawing, but that prize was divided among four ticket holders.
Illinois' ,biggest previous single-winner jackpot was $40 million,
won in 1984.
