<FIRST>r i AM-Turkey-Kurds     08-29 0119</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Turkey-Kurds,0121</SECOND>
<HEAD>Five Abducted Villagers Found Dead</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAKKARI, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Security forces on Tuesday found the
bodies of five villagers who had been kidnapped by Kurdish rebels 15
days ago in this southeastern region, the semi-official Anatolia
News Agency reported.
   The agency said the five were among nine villagers abducted from
Dilekli village in Yuksekova township. It said the rebels had freed
the other four villagers.
   Guerrillas linked with the outlawed Kurdish Labor Party have been
attacking military outposts and killing civilians and soldiers in
the area since 1984. The Marxist group seeks to set up an
independent Kurdish state in eastern and southeastern Turkey.
   Ethnic Kurds make up about one-fifth of Turkey's population of 55
million.
