<FILEID>AP-NR-08-29-89 2209EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i AM-UN-Palestinians     08-29 0100</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-UN-Palestinians,0102</SECOND>
<HEAD>Arabs Ask Security Council Meet on Expulsion of Palestinians</HEAD>
<DATELINE>UNITED NATIONS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Arab nations on Tuesday demanded an urgent
Security Council meeting to denounce Israel's deportation of five
Arabs accused of leading the Palestinian uprising in the occupied
lands.
   Qatar relayed the request to this month's council president,
Algerian Ambassador Hocine Djoudi.
   On Sunday, Israel expelled the five from the West Bank, sending
four to Lebanon and one to France.
   The Arabs ask for their return and are drafting a resolution
deploring Israel's ``flagrant violation'' of the Geneva Convention
governing protection of civilians in occupied territories.
</TEXT>
