billion in the second quarter, the best showing in more than four
years, as a record level of exports overcame a big surge in the
nation's foreign oil bill, the government says.
   The Commerce Department said Monday the 2.3 percent drop in the
trade deficit during the April-June period marked the second
consecutive quarterly decline. But economists warned that the
deficit may be growing again in the second half of the year.
