<FIRST>u f AM-OilPrices     08-29 0180</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Oil Prices,0186</SECOND>
<HEAD>Oil Futures Close Mixed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Oil futures prices ended mixed Tuesday in another
quiet day of trading.
   On the New York Mercantile Exchange, the October contract for
West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark grade of U.S. crude oil,
closed flat at $18.64 per 42-gallon barrel after a gain of 13 cents
in Monday's session. Contracts for later delivery closed lower.
   Refined products traded on the exchange posted slight gains. The
September contract for wholesale unleaded gasoline added 0.96 cent
to finish at 54.61 cents a gallon, and home heating oil for
September delivery rose 0.45 cent to close at 52.17 cents a gallon.
   Other contract months for both products were mostly higher.
   Analysts said volume picked up only slightly from Monday's
turtle-like pace, with no new developments to move the market.
   Monday's activity was the slowest of the year, with only about
21,000 crude oil contracts traded, representing 1,000 barrels per
contract. Tuesday's volume rose to about 38,000, said Evan Baron,
senior account executive with Elders Futures Inc. Normal trading
volume is about 65,000.
</TEXT>
